```plantuml
@startuml JuliaParallel_DagScheduler.jl

package "DagScheduler.jl" {
    [DagScheduler] as DS
    [common.jl] as Common
    [plugin.jl] as Plugin
    [scheduler.jl] as Scheduler
    [engine.jl] as Engine
    [queue.jl] as Queue

    package "meta_stores" {
        [ShmemMetaStore] as Shmem
        [SimpleMetaStore] as Simple
        [FDBMetaStore] as FDB
    }
}

[Node] as Node
[Broker] as Broker
[Executor] as Executor
[RemoteMonitor] as Monitor
[FoundationDB] as FDBExternal

DS --> Common : uses
DS --> Plugin : uses
DS --> Scheduler : uses
DS --> Engine : uses
DS --> Queue : uses
DS --> "meta_stores" : selects\nimplementation

Scheduler --> Engine : schedules\ntasks
Engine --> Queue : manages\ntask queues
Queue --> Executor : assigns\ntasks

"meta_stores" --> Monitor : notifies\nchanges
FDB --> FDBExternal : persists\ndata

Node --> Broker : hosts
Broker --> Executor : manages

note top of DS
    **Data Flow & Performance**
    - Tiered architecture (Node/Broker/Executor)
    minimizes central bottlenecks
    - MetaStore abstraction enables
    performance-optimized storage
    - Async I/O via Brokers prevents
    computation blocking
end note

@enduml
```